# NativeCore Framework - Cursor Rules

## Project Overview
NativeCore is a zero-dependency TypeScript SPA framework using native Web Components, a custom
History API router, reactive signals (useState/computed), lazy loading, JWT auth with a dual-shell
architecture, and Puppeteer-based bot pre-rendering for SEO.

## Critical Rules

### No Emojis
NEVER use emojis in code, console.logs, comments, or documentation. Plain text only.

### TypeScript & Imports
- Source: `src/**/*.ts` — compiled to `dist/**/*.js`
- ALWAYS use `.js` extension in imports (ES modules requirement)
- Use path aliases (`@core/`, `@services/`, `@utils/`, `@stores/`, `@components/`, `@middleware/`)
- Never import controllers at the top level — use `lazyController()` in routes

```typescript
// Correct
import { Component } from '@core/component.js';
import { trackEvents, trackSubscriptions } from '@utils/events.js';
import api from '@services/api.service.js';

// Wrong
import { Component } from '@core/component';        // Missing .js
import dashboardController from './dashboard.js';    // Direct controller import
```

## File Structure

```
src/
├── app.ts                      # Entry point — keep minimal, no logic here
├── config/routes.ts            # All route definitions
├── core/                       # Framework primitives — do not modify
│   ├── component.ts            # Base Component class
│   ├── router.ts               # SPA router with middleware
│   ├── state.ts                # useState + computed
│   ├── http.ts                 # Fetch wrapper
│   └── lazyComponents.ts       # Component registry system
├── components/
│   ├── core/                   # Layout components (app-header, app-sidebar)
│   ├── ui/                     # All nc-* reusable UI components
│   ├── registry.ts             # Component lazy loading registry
│   └── preloadRegistry.ts      # Components to preload on startup
├── controllers/
│   ├── index.ts                # Named exports for all controllers
│   └── *.controller.ts         # Page controllers
├── views/
│   ├── public/                 # HTML templates — no auth required
│   └── protected/              # HTML templates — auth required
├── services/
│   ├── api.service.ts
│   ├── auth.service.ts
│   └── logger.service.ts
├── stores/
│   ├── appStore.ts             # user, isLoading, error
│   └── uiStore.ts              # sidebarOpen, theme, notifications
├── middleware/auth.middleware.ts
├── utils/
│   ├── events.ts               # trackEvents, trackSubscriptions, delegate
│   ├── dom.ts                  # dom.query, dom.listen, dom.create, dom.within, etc.
│   ├── formatters.ts
│   ├── helpers.ts
│   └── validation.ts
├── constants/                  # apiEndpoints, routePaths, storageKeys, errorMessages
└── types/global.d.ts
```

## Naming Conventions

| Artifact    | Format                        | Example                          |
|-------------|-------------------------------|----------------------------------|
| Component   | kebab-case (hyphen required)  | `user-card.ts`, `nc-button.ts`    |
| Controller  | kebab-case.controller.ts      | `dashboard.controller.ts`        |
| View        | kebab-case.html               | `user-profile.html`              |
| Function    | camelCase + Controller suffix | `dashboardController`            |
| Store       | camelCase + Store             | `appStore`, `uiStore`            |

## Component Pattern (Shadow DOM Required)

```typescript
import { Component, defineComponent } from '@core/component.js';
import { useState, computed } from '@core/state.js';
import type { State, ComputedState } from '@core/state.js';

export class MyComponent extends Component {
    static useShadowDOM = true; // REQUIRED on all UI components

    count: State<number>;
    doubled: ComputedState<number>;

    constructor() {
        super();
        this.count = useState(0);
        this.doubled = computed(() => this.count.value * 2);
    }

    template() {
        return `
            <style>
                .container { padding: 1rem; }
            </style>
            <div class="container">
                <span id="display">${this.count.value}</span>
                <button class="increment-btn">Increment</button>
            </div>
        `;
    }

    onMount() {
        // Event delegation on shadowRoot for reliability
        this.shadowRoot.addEventListener('click', (e) => {
            if ((e.target as HTMLElement).matches('.increment-btn')) {
                this.count.value++;
            }
        });

        // Store unsubscribe so it can be cleaned up
        this._unwatchCount = this.count.watch(val => {
            this.shadowRoot.querySelector('#display')!.textContent = String(val);
        });
    }

    onUnmount() {
        // Clean up watchers
        this._unwatchCount?.();
        // Dispose computed to release dependency subscriptions
        this.doubled.dispose();
    }
}

defineComponent('my-component', MyComponent);
```

## Controller Pattern (Cleanup Required)

Every controller MUST return a cleanup function. Use `trackEvents` + `trackSubscriptions`.

```typescript
import { trackEvents, trackSubscriptions } from '@utils/events.js';
import api from '@services/api.service.js';
import { store } from '@stores/appStore.js';

export async function myPageController(params: Record<string, string> = {}): Promise<() => void> {
    const events = trackEvents();
    const subs = trackSubscriptions();

    const data = await api.get('/endpoint');

    // Render HTML into view
    document.getElementById('container')!.innerHTML = `...`;

    // Attach all events through trackEvents
    events.onClick('#save-btn', handleSave);
    events.delegate('#list', 'click', '.item', handleItemClick);
    events.on('#search', 'input', handleSearch);

    // Watch reactive state through trackSubscriptions
    subs.watch(store.isLoading.watch(loading => toggleSpinner(loading)));
    subs.watch(store.user.watch(user => renderUser(user)));

    // Always return cleanup
    return () => {
        events.cleanup();
        subs.cleanup();
    };
}
```

## Routing Pattern

```typescript
// src/config/routes.ts
import { router, lazyController } from '@core/router.js';

router
    .use(authMiddleware)
    .register('/', 'views/pages/public/home.html')
    .register('/about', 'views/pages/public/about.html')
    .register('/dashboard', 'views/pages/protected/dashboard.html',
        lazyController('dashboardController', '../controllers/dashboard.controller.js'))
    .register('/user/:id', 'views/pages/protected/user-detail.html',
        lazyController('userDetailController', '../controllers/user-detail.controller.js'));

export const protectedRoutes = ['/dashboard', '/user'];
```

## Component Registry

```typescript
// src/components/registry.ts
componentRegistry.register('my-component', './ui/my-component.js');
// All UI components use './ui/' prefix
// Loaded lazily when the tag appears in the DOM
```

## State Management

```typescript
// Local state in a component
this.count = useState(0);
this.count.value++;                        // Direct set
this.count.set(prev => prev + 1);          // Functional update
const unsub = this.count.watch(val => {}); // Returns unsubscribe

// Computed (derived, read-only)
this.total = computed(() => this.price.value * this.qty.value);
// Must call .dispose() in onUnmount to prevent memory leaks

// Global state
import { store } from '@stores/appStore.js';
store.user.value = { id: 1, name: 'Alice' };
store.isLoading.watch(loading => updateUI(loading));
```

## DOM Utilities (src/utils/dom.ts)

```typescript
import dom from '@utils/dom.js';

dom.query('#btn')                          // null-safe querySelector
dom.queryAll('.items')                     // querySelectorAll
dom.within(shadowRoot, '.child')          // scoped query in parent/shadowRoot
dom.create('div', { class: 'card' }, 'Hello') // create element with attrs + children
dom.addClass('#el', 'active')             // add CSS class
dom.removeClass('#el', 'active')          // remove CSS class
dom.toggleClass('#el', 'open')            // toggle CSS class
dom.show('#el')                           // removes display:none
dom.hide('#el')                           // sets display:none
const off = dom.listen('#btn', 'click', handler); // returns unsubscribe
off();                                    // removes listener
```

## Generator Commands

```bash
npm run make:component <name>    # Creates src/components/ui/<name>.ts + registers in registry.ts
npm run make:view <name>         # Creates view HTML + optional controller + updates routes.ts
npm run remove:component <name>  # Removes component + cleans registry
npm run remove:view <name>       # Removes view + controller + cleans routes
npm run compile                  # Compile TypeScript
npm run build                    # Production build
```

## DO

- Return a cleanup function from every controller
- Use `trackEvents()` + `trackSubscriptions()` — never attach listeners manually in controllers
- Call `computed.dispose()` in `onUnmount`
- Store `.watch()` returns and call them in `onUnmount`
- Use event delegation on `shadowRoot` in components
- Use generators (`make:component`, `make:view`) instead of creating files manually
- Use `.js` extension in all imports
- Use path aliases for cross-cutting imports

## DON'T

- Import controllers directly — use `lazyController()`
- Use `document.querySelector` in components — use `this.shadowRoot.querySelector` or `this.$()`
- Skip cleanup — memory leaks accumulate across navigations
- Add logic to `app.ts` — routes go in `config/routes.ts`
- Forget `static useShadowDOM = true` on UI components
- Use emojis anywhere

## Auth Pattern

- JWT tokens stored in `sessionStorage` (cleared when browser closes)
- Two shells: `index.html` (public) and `app.html` (protected)
- Protected routes listed in `protectedRoutes` export from `routes.ts`
- Auth check: `auth.isAuthenticated()`, user: `auth.getUser()`
- Shell mismatch triggers full page reload (router handles automatically)

## Project Overview
This is **NativeCore** (formerly NFBS) - a modern **TypeScript SPA framework** with:
- Zero runtime dependencies
- Web Components with Shadow DOM
- Custom router with lazy loading
- Reactive state management (signals: useState, computed)
- JWT authentication with dual-shell architecture
- Bot-optimized SEO (pre-rendered HTML)
- Component and view generators
- Path aliases with tsc-alias

## Architecture Principles

### 1. **Separation of Concerns**
- `src/app.ts` - Minimal entry point, only initialization
- `src/config/routes.ts` - All route definitions
- `src/middleware/` - Request/response middleware
- `src/controllers/` - Page-specific logic
- `src/components/core/` - Layout components (header, sidebar, footer)
- `src/components/ui/` - Reusable UI components (nc-button, nc-card, etc.)
- `src/core/` - Framework primitives (router, signals, http, etc.)
- `src/utils/` - Helper functions
- `src/constants/` - App constants (API endpoints, routes, etc.)
- `src/stores/` - Global state stores
- `src/services/` - API, auth, logger services

### 2. **Lazy Loading Strategy**
- **Controllers**: Lazy loaded via dynamic imports with `lazyController()`
- **Components**: Registry-based lazy loading in `components/registry.ts`
- **HTML Views**: Fetched on route access
- **Critical components**: Preloaded in `components/preloadRegistry.ts`

### 3. **Naming Conventions**
- **Components**: kebab-case with hyphen (e.g., `user-card`, `nc-button`)
- **Controllers**: camelCase with "Controller" suffix (e.g., `dashboardController`)
- **Files**: TypeScript `.ts` extension (e.g., `user-card.ts`, `dashboard.controller.ts`)
- **Views**: kebab-case HTML files (e.g., `user-profile.html`)

